WEBVTT

00:01:59.508 --> 00:02:01.461
mercenaries became freelancers

00:02:01.485 --> 00:02:04.081
to escape the iron rule
of oppressive kingdoms.

00:02:04.746 --> 00:02:06.150
During the Renaissance,

00:02:06.174 --> 00:02:09.502
apprentices ditched their mentors
to take charge of their own crafts.

00:02:10.114 --> 00:02:13.399
And now, we have more and more
people working for themselves.

00:02:14.034 --> 00:02:16.223
Across the United States
and Western Europe,

00:02:16.247 --> 00:02:19.527
there are about 150 million
independent workers.

00:02:20.722 --> 00:02:24.960
Dan Pink anticipated that trend
back in the late 1990s,

00:02:24.984 --> 00:02:27.489
long before the gig economy
started booming.

00:02:27.934 --> 00:02:29.638
He quit his job at the White House

00:02:29.662 --> 00:02:32.420
to study people who
are working for themselves,